description.plain:
Terrell Cox (born May 29, 1999), better know by his stage name Cochise (formerly Yung Cochise), is an up-and-coming rapper who first gained attention from his guest appearance on DBangz' popular December 2017 meme rap song “LET A NIGGA SMASH.”

Cochise released his debut mixtape PULP on May 3, 2018. He later released his collab EP with Lousho, Hijack, a year later on August 23, 2019.

Besides his 2017 collab with DBangz, Cochise is known for his solo songs as well, such as “Dig Me Freestyle,” “Hatchback,” and his breakout single “Red Head,” which would gain even more attention thanks to it going viral on TikTok.

Cochise signed a record deal with Columbia Records in June of 2020 due to the viral success of his song “Hatchback.”

On May 7, 2021, Cochise released his debut album, Benbow Crescent.

songs.title: Hatchback

description.plain:
“Hatchback” is the breakout song by Cochise. Originally being released on September 26, 2019, the song wouldn’t really take off until June of 2020 when it went viral on TikTok, similarly to Cochise’s song “Red Head” and his guest appearance on DBangz' song “LET A NIGGA SMASH,” which also went viral on TikTok.

Due to the viral success of “Hatchback,” Cochise signed a record deal with Columbia Records.

songs.title: Red Head

description.plain:
Red Head is the breakout hit made by rapper Cochise.

This song went viral on TikTok, mainly for his baby-voiced last verse, debatably starting a new trend in SoundCloud rap.

songs.title: POCKET ROCKET

description.plain:
“Pocket Rocket” is a single by Florida rapper Cochise.

Previewed in October 2020, the song was very sought out by the fans as they continuously asked Cochise to release the song as he previewed it many times.

On August 18th, 2021, Cochise confirmed the song’s release date and music video for August 20th, 2021.
